snippet: The Commerce Department said on Monday that sales dropped 11.5 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 468,000 units, the lowest level since November 2014.
abstract: Commerce Department says sales of new single-family homes in United States fell 11.5 percent in September to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 468,000 units, lowest level since November 2014; notes that jump in prices suggests solid housing market nonetheless.
lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department said on Monday that sales dropped 11.5 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 468,000 units, the lowest level since November 2014.

headline.print_headline: Business Briefing; Economists Unfazed by Slump in Sales of New Homes
headline.main: New-Home Sales Fall to Near One-Year Low
